# SDUI JSON Configuration

This project uses JSON-driven UI with composition. **Never hardcode layout or shared UI in React**—define everything in JSON.

## Layouts
- Use `layout: "authenticated"` in screen config to wrap content with shared header + drawer
- Layouts live in `config/layouts/` and define structure with `$ref` and `$slot`
- Add new layouts in `config/layouts/` and register in `layouts/index.ts`

## Fragments ($ref)
- Reusable UI pieces: `"$ref": "fragments/header"`, `"$ref": "fragments/drawer"`, `"$ref": "fragments/modals/createProduct"`
- Add fragments in `config/fragments/` and register in `fragments/index.ts`
- Fragments can contain `{{variable}}` interpolation (e.g. `{{meta.title}}`, `{{layout.drawerOpen}}`)

## Navigation (no hardcoded paths)
- Static: `{ "action": "navigate", "payload": { "path": "/shop" } }`
- Dynamic (e.g. product detail): `{ "action": "navigate", "payload": { "routeConfig": "product", "slug": { "var": "$item.slug" } } }`—route path comes from `config/routes.json`.

## Theme & Colors
- Use theme variables: `text-[var(--theme-header-text)]`, `bg-[var(--theme-announcement-bg)]`—never hardcoded hex colors.
- Theme defined in `config/theme.json` (colors, sections.announcement, sections.header, sections.hero).

## Content Slot
- Layouts use `"$slot": "content"` as placeholder; screen `content` is injected there
- `content` can be a single node or array (e.g. main content + modals)

## Reusing Modals
- Extract modals to `config/fragments/modals/` and reference with `$ref`
- Same modal fragment can be used across screens that share state paths (e.g. `modal.create`)

## Screen Structure
```json
{
  "meta": { "title": "..." },
  "state": { ... },
  "layout": "authenticated",
  "content": { ... } or [ ... ],
  "initActions": [ ... ]
}
```
Screens without `layout` use `ui` directly (e.g. login, signup).
